    "summary": "Since 1982 I have been established as freelance photographer and audiovisual designer, combining commercial assignments with free art work. Ever since, my photo-work has been published in books, reports and other publications. My audiovisual work developed from slide-shows for educational programmes to producing video-walls for the Dutch Ministry of Development Cooperation. Recently I experimented with large size photo-prints for exhibitions and events on industrial heritage. My art work has been exhibited in museums in Eastern and Western Europe as well as in Africa. Since 2006 curator for BredaPhoto international photo festival \n\nI have been commissioned assignments by the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the Ministry for Housing, Spatial Planning and Environment, the Royal Tropical Institute, Dutch development cooperation organisations and ethnographical museums. This required travelling over most continents: Africa, Asia, the Middle East and Latin America. \n\nIn all my work I try to combine subject matter with human interest and interaction. I am fascinated and inspired by daily recurring events in the lives of ordinary people; how they live, eat, drink, work, sleep, dream and love. \n\nPhotography and film projects in the Netherlands and across the world. Image design and production of documentaries, business reports, information brochures and all that good photography may mean an added to the final result.\n\nSince 2011 I have been working on my longterm photo project 'Eboundja' \nfacebook eboundja\nInstagram reinout_van_den_bergh\n \n\nSpecialties: Since 1997 I work with the sculptor Huib Fens to the project 'Factories'. Industrial heritage and its relation with economic and social development. \n\n1981-1991 I worked together with Gerhard Lentink, sculptor, on different Environmental projects; Circulus, Mezalocha, Callejones de Toledo, Upptyppingar and Filabres",
